{"type":"message","id":"bc8cd81b","parentId":"706e99cd","timestamp":"2026-05-10T13:19:52.979Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is saying the format of my replies is wrong - it's missing the model name header and the footer isn't complete. They're asking why the format changed. \n\nLooking at my previous reply, I did follow the format: `🧑🏼‍💻[MODEL] [ประเภท] 🧑🏼‍💻` at the top and `[Tokens: ระดับ | Cache: X% | RTK: ...]` + `🧑🏼‍💻` at the bottom.\n\nWait, but in my reply I said `[Tokens: ต่ำ | RTK: -]` but actually the format should say `[Tokens: ระดับ | Cache: X% | RTK: ...]`. Let me re-read my format from AGENTS.md:\n\n\n- Header: `🧑🏼‍💻[MODEL] [คำถามทั่วไป/ทำงาน/สรุป] 🧑🏼‍💻`\n- Footer: `[Tokens: ระดับ | Cache: X% | RTK: ...]` แล้วปิด `🧑🏼‍💻`\n\nSo my last reply was `🧑🏼‍💻[ทำงาน] 🧑🏼‍💻` followed by the body and then `[Tokens: ต่ำ | RTK: -] 🧑🏼‍💻` - but I need to check if I'm using the correct token level indicators.\n\nActually, I'm realizing the header format should include the model name too - I was just using the task type when it should be `🧑🏼‍💻[MODEL] [ประเภท] 🧑🏼‍💻`. And for the footer, I'm missing the Cache percentage entirely. Looking at the MEMORY.md I do have default model info: `Current model display: openai-codex/gpt-5.5 → GPT 5.5`. Let me check what my session status shows about the current model and fix the format accordingly.\n","thinkingSignature":"a1c29d0ea2ded6454271c4808d9fc67f50c4630e990de58b13e737dc1da03ef5"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_f12e5ikcsepy_1","name":"session_status","arguments":{}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":27921,"output":458,"cacheRead":192,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":28571,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778419169801,"responseId":"064fb8e3c5f2b0ff1ecad7a2eae8fafa"}}
