{"type":"message","id":"250dabcf","parentId":"1b957aef","timestamp":"2026-05-10T13:29:15.183Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see sessions.json is 430.1K - that's a large file. Let me check the sessions.json to understand the session storage. The file `sessions.json` likely contains the session registry. Let me see how many sessions are stored in there and if old sessions are being cleaned up.\n\nThe user's complaint is clear: they set up session retention rules (rolling 2 sessions) but sessions are still disappearing. They want to know where their sessions went.\n\nLet me check `sessions.json` to see if old sessions are actually registered there or if they're being deleted.","thinkingSignature":"9446da910c04f42242dd1865171c4feecbfce8e1a82e5518171fab7c73117d81"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_knrdz58i72ux_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /home/apinan/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/sessions.json | python3 -c \"import json,sys; data=json.load(sys.stdin); print(f'Total sessions: {len(data)}'); [print(k) for k in data.keys()]\" 2>/dev/null | head -30"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":563,"output":205,"cacheRead":30560,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":31328,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778419749054,"responseId":"064fbb260cae1a09ee9f87f641e7621c"}}
