{"type":"message","id":"01ac8dbe","parentId":"5f596091","timestamp":"2026-05-10T13:29:30.666Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I can see what's happening! The `sessions.json` contains 11 sessions, but `sessions_list` only shows 1. Let me check what's going on with the other sessions. I see:\n- `agent:main:telegram:direct:robberzaz` - current one\n- `agent:main:telegram:direct:1060942816` - another one\n- `agent:main:telegram:default:direct:1060942816` - another\n\nThere are multiple sessions for the same Telegram user. The issue might be that `sessions_list` is filtering based on the current inbound context (which shows `sender_id: \"1060942816\"`), but the sessions are stored under different keys.\n \nThe `sessions_list` API appears to be filtering by the inbound metadata, which would explain why it's only returning one session when there are actually multiple stored in the sessions.json file.\n","thinkingSignature":"9f0df404ecb18ac9a44ef0c31fe73741ebbcfd0f98493574245793dbedb4f4b7"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_lr9xbp10hm81_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /home/apinan/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/sessions.json | python3 -c \"\nimport json,sys\ndata=json.load(sys.stdin)\nfor k,v in data.items():\n    print(f'{k}')\n    print(f'  sessionId: {v.get(\\\"sessionId\\\",\\\"\\\")}')\n    print(f'  lastMessage: {v.get(\\\"lastMessage\\\",\\\"\\\")[:80] if v.get(\\\"lastMessage\\\") else \\\"\\\"}')\n    print()\n\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":333,"output":311,"cacheRead":31104,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":31748,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778419755238,"responseId":"064fbb2cbf681cd9eab876779dfa5fee"}}
